headline: Snowflake (SNOW) Is Up 8.2% After Deepening OpenAI Tie-Up And Unveiling New AI Tools - What's Changed
summary: In early February 2026, Snowflake announced a multi‑year US$200.00 million collaboration with OpenAI and rolled out new AI capabilities, including Cortex Code, Semantic View Autopilot, expanded Postgres support, and deeper integrations with partners and customers such as United Rentals, Experian, Wolfspeed, and RESAAS. Together, these moves highlight Snowflake’s push to become an AI-native data foundation where enterprises can run governed, production-grade AI agents and workflows directly...
